\nr<Galathan><Wrap>What will you say to her when you see her, your Majesty?
\n<Alex><Wrap>That I've missed her. That I love her. That I'll always love her.
\n<Alex><Wrap>I have to, I need to know if there are any updates from Sir Esther. He should have been back by now. And the High Council requires my presence.
\nr<Sharon><Wrap>Will you come to me when the candle burns low?
\n<Baenor><Wrap>The wounds don’t look so great, but they are as bound as they ever will be.
\n<Alex><Wrap>Yes, Sir Galathan. It isn’t too much further.
\n<Alex><Wrap>Sir Esther... you can’t know how sorry I am, how sorry I have always been-
\n<Alex><Wrap>No, it won’t. Do you mean to kill me? Time has beaten you to it, I’m afraid.
\n<Esther><Wrap>What I want is to make sure you don’t see HER again.
\n<Alex><Wrap>I had to try to save her. I had to. I was desperate and the attempt cost more than I had ever imagined it would, and for that I will always be so sorry. To both you and Liliana.
\n<Esther><Wrap>You keep her name out of your lying mouth!
\n<Esther><Wrap>Do you hear her? She’s singing again... "Down by the river... The river so blue..."
\n<Baenor><Wrap>His mind is addled, Majesty, we should not linger.
\n<Esther><Wrap>You escaped me before, but now there is nowhere for you run. There is no more Thomas to stop me from following you.
\n<Nathan><Wrap>I... don't think i'm doing so well...
\n<Baenor><Wrap>His wounds are reopened, and he sustained plenty of new ones... I’ll do what I can.
\nr<Galathan><Wrap>Majesty, isn’t Candle Point just up ahead?
\nr<Galathan><Wrap>Master Baenor, Dame Alyssa, look after Sir Nathan. I will escort his Majesty the rest of the way.
